An e-commerce platform runs a single Task Queue called `order-processing` shared by payment workflows (priority 1), inventory workflows (priority 3), and analytics batch jobs (priority 5). The team now wants to ensure that among priority-3 inventory workflows, three large vendors don't starve five smaller vendors. They assign fairness keys per vendor with weights: large vendors get 3.0, small vendors get 1.0. After enabling Fairness in production (Temporal Cloud), an engineer notices that even with the fairness weights configured, the large vendors are still consuming the majority of Worker capacity for several minutes after a burst. Which statement best explains this observed behavior?

Relevant Go snippet:
```go
ao := workflow.ActivityOptions{
  StartToCloseTimeout: time.Minute,
  Priority: temporal.Priority{
    PriorityKey:    3,
    FairnessKey:    vendorID,
    FairnessWeight: vendorWeight,
  },
}
```
